dmenu-math - dynamic menu with math expression support
======================================================
dmenu-math is a fork of dmenu, an efficient dynamic menu for X.
It supports both being the standard dmenu application launcher and a math expression parser using tinyexpr.


Requirements
------------
In order to build dmenu-math you need the Xlib header files.
xclip is required for expression results to be copied into your clipboard.


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk to match your local setup (dmenu-math is installed
into the /usr/local namespace by default).

Afterwards enter the following command to build and install dmenu-math
(if necessary as root):

    make clean install


Running dmenu-math
------------------
See the man page for details.
